snippet: SolarCity, a provider of solar power to retail customers, formally disclosed its initial public offering prospectus on Monday. The company said that it plans to raise up to $201.3 million, though it gave no price range.
abstract: SolarCity, a provider of solar power to retail customers, formally disclosed its initial public offering prospectus on Monday. The company said that it plans to raise up to $201.3 million, though it gave no price range.

byline.original: By MICHAEL J. DE LA MERCED

headline.main: SolarCity Seeks Up to $201 Million in I.P.O.
